cs.NI, cs.GT, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM

This paper deals with the optimization of user access mode selection in Fog Radio Access Networks (F-RANs), which is a subfield of wireless communication networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also uses evolutionary game theory to model the competition among groups of potential users, which falls under the category of cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). Additionally, the paper uses stochastic geometry tools to derive the proposals' payoff expressions, which is a subfield of cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also deals with performance optimization, which falls under the category of cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper mentions the use of cache sizes, which is a subfield of cs.MM (Multimedia).
